    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-03-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <head>No. 467.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Brown</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-03-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 21,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 50, of the 16th ultimo,
                            has been received. Your course in behalf of the American College of
                            Medicine at Beirut is approved. The privileges conferred upon that
                            college are doubtless favorable, and apparently all that could be
                            obtained.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">HAMILTON FISH.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
